Merge branch 'mr/recognize-llvm-mingw-target' into 'master'

Recognize LLVM's canonical target for MinGW

See merge request eng/gpr/gprconfig_kb!28

Recognize LLVM's canonical target for MinGW

LLVM translates our Windows triplets to x86_64-{pc,w64}-windows-gnu.

Issue: eng/toolchain/gnatbugs-support#11

Merge branch 'mr/support-llvm-morello-elf' into 'master'

Support targeting morello-elf with LLVM

See merge request eng/gpr/gprconfig_kb!27

Support targeting morello-elf with LLVM

The LLVM representation of "morello-elf" is
"morello-unknown-unknown-elf". Since our LLVM packages are still based
on GNU binutils, which don't have an "llvm-" prefix, we can't use the
generic prefix-based rule to define the archive builder and indexer
binaries.

Issue: eng/projects/sabd/sabd#7

Merge branch 'mr/jicquel/246-group-string' into 'master'

Set "group" type of <directory> node as "string" instead of "positive or default"

See merge request eng/gpr/gprconfig_kb!23

Set "group" type of <directory> node as "string" instead of "positive or default"

The group value restriction was too restrictive compared to what we want
to achieve. If group is a string, we want to return that string on
match.

Merge branch 'W410-007-aarch64-linux-nat-binutils' into 'master'

Use correct binutils on native aarch64-linux

See merge request eng/gpr/gprconfig_kb!13

Use correct binutils on native aarch64-linux

The current KB tells gprbuild to use tools prefixed with
"aarch64-linux-gnu-", which our native toolchain does not provide.  We end
up using the system binutils instead, which do not perform adequately.

TN: W410-007
